This paper deals with wireless networks and their protocols, which are typically studied in the computer science sub-category of Network and Internet Architecture (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the throughput and delay scaling laws, which are related to information theory (cs.IT). The use of cognitive radio technologies and the consideration of mobility models suggest that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-categories of Multi-Agent Systems (cs.MA) and Systems and Control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper deals with interference management, which is a key aspect of Cognitive Radio (cs.CR).
